commit.message:
configure: fix typo in command name that prevented effectively running (#205)

The check was for dpkg-architecture, but actually running it would elide
the "i".

Detected on Gentoo (!!!) with dpkg coincidentally installed, because it
is logged as a QA warning:

```
 * QA Notice: command not found:
 *
 *      ./configure: 19734: dpkg-archtecture: not found
 *      ./configure: 19942: dpkg-archtecture: not found
 ```

configure: Fix snprintf check for strict(er) C99 compilers (#187)

C99 removed support for implicit function declarations. The test calls
the undeclared exit function, so it may fail incorrectly with C99
compilers. Return from main instead to report the test result.

uim-fep 24bit color support (#180)

Fixed a bug in vim that uim-fep's preedit becomes the color of vim's
status line.
Fixed to restore 24bit color and 256 color attributes after preedit
editing is done.
Added 256 colors and 24 bit colors settings to the -C option.

Add workaround for intltoolize

GitHub: fix GH-179

Reported by calimeroteknik. Thanks!!!

uim-xim: Don't hardcode fontsets at compile-time (#177)

This change moves the default fontset definitions to im-custom.scm so
that users may define the fontsets and avoid stderr being filled with:
Critical: XCreateFontSet failed!

Users can override fontsets in ~/.uim or under ~/.uim.d/customs.
Packagers may choose to ship with different fontsets by changing the
defaults under ${datarootdir}/uim.

commit.message:
Stop support for regenerating scm/json-parser-expanded.scm

GitHub: fix GH-26

Because Chicken 4 or later doesn't support syntax-case. We can still
use bundled scm/json-parser-expanded.scm without support for
regenerating scm/json-parser-expanded.scm. But if we find a problem
with the current scm/json-parser-expanded.scm, we need to modify the
file directly or replace it with other implementation.

Reported by Reuben Thomas. Thanks!!!
